Class JED_Get_Subspace_Analysis

  • java.lang.Object
    • jed.JED_Get_Subspace_Analysis

  • public class JED_Get_Subspace_Analysis

    JED class JED_Get_Subspace_Analysis: Performs Subspace Analysis on sets of eigenvectors with varying degree of outputs.       Constructor and Description
      JED_Get_Subspace_Analysis(java.lang.String dir, java.lang.String desc, java.lang.String type_pca, Jama.Matrix evects1, Jama.Matrix evects2, java.lang.String variant)
      Constructor for performing Subspace Analysis Note: The matrices of eigenvectors must have the same dimensions for both rows and columns.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void get_FSSA_Iterated_JED()
      Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the FSSA Iterated method: This iteratively compares the two subspaces using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO, CP, and VAS.
      void get_Random_FSSA_JED()
      Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the Random FSSA method: This compares two random subspaces having the same dim as the entered ones, using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO.
      void get_SSA_JED()
      Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the SSA method: This compares the two subspaces directly using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO, CP, and VAS.

        Constructor for performing Subspace Analysis Note: The matrices of eigenvectors must have the same dimensions for both rows and columns.
        Parameters:
        dir - The working directory
        desc - The job description
        type_pca - The type of PCA: COV or CORR (Q or R)
        evects1 - The first set of eigenvectors for the subspace comparison
        evects2 - The second set of eigenvectors for the subspace comparison

    • Method Detail

      • get_SSA_JED

        public void get_SSA_JED()
        Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the SSA method: This compares the two subspaces directly using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO, CP, and VAS.

      • get_FSSA_Iterated_JED

        public void get_FSSA_Iterated_JED()
        Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the FSSA Iterated method: This iteratively compares the two subspaces using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO, CP, and VAS. Comparisons are made for SS dims from 1 to the entered dim.

      • get_Random_FSSA_JED

        public void get_Random_FSSA_JED()
        Calls the Subspace Analysis class and runs the Random FSSA method: This compares two random subspaces having the same dim as the entered ones, using the metrics of RMSIP, PA, CO.
